{"id": "920574", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=920574", "title": "Gloves of the Pugilist", "text": ""}
{"id": "45161", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45161", "title": "Gloves of the Pugilist (Skyrim)", "text": "Gloves of the Pugilist are a unique pair of &lt;a href=\"Fur%20Gauntlets%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;fur gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; found in . They boost damage done by &lt;a href=\"Unarmed%20Combat%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;unarmed attacks&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nThey are worn by &lt;a href=\"Gian%20the%20Fist\"&gt;Gian the Fist&lt;/a&gt;, who can be found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ratway\"&gt;The Ratway&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;a href=\"Riften%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Riften&lt;/a&gt;. After killing the two bandits near the entrance of the Ratway, continue down the hall and jump off the path where the bridge is, take a right once down by the bridge and keep following that path. Gian the Fist is located in a room full of bear traps. He will attack upon sight, but once defeated he can be looted to receive the Gloves of the Pugilist.\nEnchantment.\nThis pair of gloves is the only item that bears the &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Unarmed\"&gt;Fortify Unarmed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20Effects\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt;, and thus the only item that the enchantment can be learned from; there are no randomly generated pieces that possess this enchantment. The enchantment can only be placed on &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;rings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Clothing%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;gloves&lt;/a&gt;, or gauntlets.\nSmithing.\nThey can be upgraded at a &lt;a href=\"workbench\"&gt;workbench&lt;/a&gt; with a piece of &lt;a href=\"Leather%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;leather&lt;/a&gt;, however, they do not benefit from any &lt;a href=\"Smithing%20%28Skyrim%29%23Perks\"&gt;Smithing perks&lt;/a&gt;. This means they cannot be improved past &lt;a href=\"Smithing%20%28Skyrim%29%23Improvement\"&gt;flawless&lt;/a&gt; quality without boosting the Smithing skill over 100. This can be achieved by using &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Smithing%23Enchanting\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; items and/or &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Smithing%23Potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"fortify%20Smithing\"&gt;fortify Smithing&lt;/a&gt;."}
