{"id": "11084", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11084", "title": "Gnarl", "text": "Gnarls, also referred to as the \"Walking Tree\" are large tree-like creatures that use both &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; and physical force in their attacks. They can be found wandering &lt;a href=\"Dementia\"&gt;Dementia&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mania\"&gt;Mania&lt;/a&gt;, however, most of their burrows can be found within Mania.\nPhysical appearance.\nWhen threatened, Gnarls usually open combat with a &lt;a href=\"Silence%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; spell. They are able to resist &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Damage%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Damage%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;frost&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Shock%20Damage%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;shock damage&lt;/a&gt;. If they are hit with a fire spell or weapon, they will grow in size and become much stronger, resisting that type of magic. This effect typically takes place for a short period of time. Even though Gnarls can be silenced, they will still throw their silence spells, making them resistant to silence. They drop &lt;a href=\"Gnarl%20Bark\"&gt;Gnarl Bark&lt;/a&gt; and sometimes &lt;a href=\"Amber%20%28Shivering%20Isles%29\"&gt;Amber&lt;/a&gt;. Their homes often have amber deposits and are defended by organic &lt;a href=\"Traps%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;traps&lt;/a&gt;.\nElder gnarls are the strongest of their kind; they have a large amount of health and a long lasting-Silence spell. They are white in &lt;a href=\"Mania\"&gt;Mania&lt;/a&gt; and darker in color in &lt;a href=\"Dementia\"&gt;Dementia&lt;/a&gt;. They somewhat resemble the &lt;a href=\"Spriggan%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Spriggan&lt;/a&gt; which inhabits &lt;a href=\"Tamriel\"&gt;Tamriel&lt;/a&gt;."}
