{"id": "90186", "revid": "44356307", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90186", "title": "Gnisis Eggmine (Location)", "text": "Gnisis Eggmine is a &lt;a href=\"Mines%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;mine&lt;/a&gt; above the city of &lt;a href=\"Gnisis%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Gnisis&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Vvardenfell%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Vvardenfell&lt;/a&gt;.\nSublocations.\nLower Eggmine.\nThe Lower Eggmine can be reached through a door in Gnisis Eggmine. Upon entering, &lt;a href=\"Lugrub%20gro-Ogdum\"&gt;Lugrub gro-Ogdum&lt;/a&gt; will give the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; little time to leave before he attacks. Apart from several hostile &lt;a href=\"Kwama%20Warrior%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Kwama warriors&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Kwama%20Queen%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Kwama Queen&lt;/a&gt; which must be cured from &lt;a href=\"blight\"&gt;blight&lt;/a&gt; during the quest \"Gnisis Eggmine\" can be found here. The Underground Stream and &lt;a href=\"Bethamez%20%28Location%29\"&gt;Bethamez&lt;/a&gt; are accessible from the Lower Eggmine.\nUnderground Stream.\nTwo doors lead from the Lower Eggmine to the Underground Stream. Here the Nerevarine encounters the ghost of &lt;a href=\"Mansilamat%20Vabdas\"&gt;Mansilamat Vabdas&lt;/a&gt; and can find his body beside &lt;a href=\"Lugrub%27s%20Axe\"&gt;Lugrub's Axe&lt;/a&gt;, which serves as proof of Vabdas' assassination by &lt;a href=\"Lugrub%20gro-Ogdum\"&gt;Lugrub gro-Ogdum&lt;/a&gt; in the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Widow%20Vabdas%27%20Deed\"&gt;Widow Vabdas' Deed&lt;/a&gt;.\" The Underground Stream ends in an underwater door, which leads to the river outside of &lt;a href=\"Gnisis%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Gnisis&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Bethamez%20%28Location%29\"&gt;Bethamez&lt;/a&gt;.\nBethamez is accessible through a door in the Lower Eggmine. It is a small &lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20Ruins%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Dwemer Ruin&lt;/a&gt; containing the unique book \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Metaphysics\"&gt;Divine Metaphysics&lt;/a&gt;\", as well as\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20Airship%20Plans\"&gt;Dwemer Airship Plans&lt;/a&gt;. These are connected with the quests &lt;a href=\"Mystery%20of%20the%20Dwarves\"&gt;Mystery of the Dwarves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bethamez%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Bethamez&lt;/a&gt;, respectively."}
{"id": "90187", "revid": "5165253", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90187", "title": "Gnisis Eggmine (Quest)", "text": "Gnisis Eggmine is an &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Legion%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Imperial Legion&lt;/a&gt; quest available in .\nBackground.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Kwama%20Queen%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Kwama Queen&lt;/a&gt; in the local mine in &lt;a href=\"Gnisis%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Gnisis&lt;/a&gt; has been blighted and the mine has thus been shut down. As the eggmine is the most important economic element in Gnisis, the local population suffers greatly. Therefore, General Darius sends the Nerevarine to try and cure the queen, thus restarting the local economy.\nWalkthrough.\nAfter finishing the first Imperial Legion Quest \"&lt;a href=\"Widow%20Vabdas%27%20Deed\"&gt;Widow Vabdas' Deed&lt;/a&gt;,\" talking to General Darius about orders starts the quest. If the Nerevarine has no spell or scroll to cure the Kwama Queen, he can visit &lt;a href=\"Hetman%20Abelmawia\"&gt;Hetman Abelmawia&lt;/a&gt; to buy a &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Daerir%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;Scroll of Daerir's Blessing&lt;/a&gt;. Once inside the Eggmine, the Nerevarine must head for the lower eggmine, where the queen resides. There, he must fight the several &lt;a href=\"Kwama%20Warrior%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Kwama Warriors&lt;/a&gt; guarding the queen. Once the queen has been healed, the Nerevarine should return to Darius to receive his reward.\nRewards.\n100"}
