{"id": "653648", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=653648", "title": "Goblin (Arena)", "text": "Goblins are &lt;a href=\"Creatures%20%28Arena%29\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt; encountered in .\nOverview.\nGoblins are yellow colored, little and imbecile creatures who inhabit dungeons and use axes of their own stature to fight. Goblins may appear weak on the first sight, however they can also be deadly enemies to inexperienced explorers.\nGoblins are one of the first enemies to appear in the game, being opponents in the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Imperial Dungeons&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the gain of experience by the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Champion\"&gt;Eternal Champion&lt;/a&gt;, Goblins stop being a dangerous creature and become insignificant.\nGoblins are encountered mainly in dungeons, however they can also appear at night outside and inside cities."}
{"id": "1043415", "revid": "26893431", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1043415", "title": "Goblin (Blades)", "text": "Goblins are small humanoid creatures that appear in . They are encountered by the &lt;a href=\"Fugitive%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;Fugitive&lt;/a&gt; during their quests.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Rescuing%20the%20Townsfolk\"&gt;Rescuing the Townsfolk&lt;/a&gt;.\nA number of Goblins took over the abandoned &lt;a href=\"Highwinter%20Castle\"&gt;Highwinter Castle&lt;/a&gt; where citizens of the &lt;a href=\"Town%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;Town&lt;/a&gt; were being held captive by them. The Fugitive must infiltrate the castle and free the townsfolk.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Goblin%20Scourge\"&gt;The Goblin Scourge&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Fugitive is tasked with killing Goblins sighted in the area near the Town in order to reduce their numbers.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Red%20and%20the%20White\"&gt;The Red and the White&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Fugitive is sent to a patch of forest which has been overrun by a goblin alliance of the Red Fang and White Ghost tribes."}
