{"id": "1096357", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1096357", "title": "Goblin Demonstration", "text": "Goblin Demonstration is a &lt;a href=\"repeatable%20quest\"&gt;repeatable quest&lt;/a&gt; in wherein the &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; must assist in training members of the &lt;a href=\"Elsweyr%20Defense%20Force\"&gt;Elsweyr Defense Force&lt;/a&gt; by demonstrating how to kill &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Online%29\"&gt;goblins&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\n\"Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.\"\nWalkthrough.\nAfter completing the prologue quest \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Halls%20of%20Colossus%20%28Online%20Quest%29\"&gt;The Halls of Colossus&lt;/a&gt;,\" you can speak to Zahari at the gate leading to &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Elsweyr\"&gt;Northern Elsweyr&lt;/a&gt; north of &lt;a href=\"Cormount%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Courmount&lt;/a&gt;. She will only give one out of a number of possible quests, one of which is to help train recruits to fight against goblins.\nHow can I help? \"Our new recruits are eager for blood, but have seen little of the battlefield. They need the aid of an experienced warrior if ever they are to become true soldiers. A warrior such as yourself, yes?\"\nAfter speaking with Zahari, you will need to proceed to the &lt;a href=\"Stonechewer%20Goblin%20Camp\"&gt;Stonechewer Goblin Camp&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Stormhaven%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Stormhaven&lt;/a&gt; northwest from &lt;a href=\"Wayrest%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Wayrest&lt;/a&gt;. When you arrive, you will need to speak with Captain Shideya who will provide a Khajiiti Recruit as a follower, and with them in tow, you will then need to kill nine goblins in the camp.\n\"Welcome, walker. You have come to show our warriors how to fight, yes?\"\nAfter killing nine goblins, the Recruit will leave, and you can immediately return to Zahari in Grahtwood to finish the quest. Zahari will thank you for your service and provide a reward.\n\"So you've returned. Has your assignment been completed?\""}
