{"id": "918934", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=918934", "title": "Godrun's Dream", "text": "Godrun's Dream may refer to:"}
{"id": "853273", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=853273", "title": "Godrun's Dream (Quest)", "text": "Godrun's Dream is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . The &lt;a href=\"Omen%20of%20Betrayal\"&gt;Omen of Betrayal&lt;/a&gt; failed to manipulate &lt;a href=\"General%20Godrun\"&gt;General Godrun&lt;/a&gt; into attacking &lt;a href=\"Wayrest%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Wayrest&lt;/a&gt;, but has now trapped General Godrun within &lt;a href=\"Godrun%27s%20Dream%20%28Location%29\"&gt;his dream&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Abbot%20Durak\"&gt;Abbot Durak&lt;/a&gt; has asked me to enter the dream and kill the Omen to save Godrun.\nWalkthrough.\nUpon completing &lt;a href=\"Ending%20the%20Ogre%20Threat\"&gt;Ending the Ogre Threat&lt;/a&gt;, head upstairs and you will find &lt;a href=\"Abbot%20Durak\"&gt;Abbot Durak&lt;/a&gt; standing over a sleeping &lt;a href=\"General%20Godrun\"&gt;General Godrun&lt;/a&gt;. Durak will tell you that the &lt;a href=\"Omen%20of%20Betrayal\"&gt;Omen of Betrayal&lt;/a&gt; has taken hold of Godrun. The Omen was planning to make Godrun betray &lt;a href=\"High%20King%20Emeric%20%28Online%29\"&gt;King Emeric&lt;/a&gt; after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Ironhand%20Ogres\"&gt;Ironhand Ogres&lt;/a&gt;, but because of how quickly you dealt with the ogres, the Omen had to enact its plans prematurely. Durak will ask you to enter the general's dreams and deal with the Omen as you have before. \nEnter Godrun's dream. It will be dark and you will be set upon by a lot of &lt;a href=\"Spectre%20of%20Treachery\"&gt;Spectres of Treachery&lt;/a&gt;, so come prepared. You will find a table ahead with a document called Godrun's Orders; interacting with it will cause a vision where Godrun orders his underlings to ask for more troops. Follow Godrun from here through a mirror of &lt;a href=\"Vaermina%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Vaermina&lt;/a&gt; and you will end up in a long passage way with even more spectres. At the end, there will be another vision, where he tells an underling that his real plan with the reinforcements is to use them against &lt;a href=\"High%20King%20Emeric%20%28Online%29\"&gt;High King Emeric&lt;/a&gt;. He will then head through another mirror; follow him again and fight through some more shades to reach the final vision, where you see Godrun making a deal with the &lt;a href=\"Supernal%20Dreamers\"&gt;Supernal Dreamers&lt;/a&gt;. \nAfter the final vision, a corporeal version of Godrun will appear; rescue him and the Omen itself will attack you. Once you have defeated it, Vaermina will speak to you. She will tell you to come to her statue within the dream; Speak with it and Vaermina will reveal that the Omens were mere distractions; her real target was High King Emeric.\nA new mirror will appear; head through and bring Durak the bad news to finish the quest and start the next one, \"&lt;a href=\"Azura%27s%20Aid\"&gt;Azura's Aid&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
