{"id": "168731", "revid": "30169600", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=168731", "title": "Shrouded Gloves", "text": "Shrouded Gloves are a piece of &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;light armor&lt;/a&gt; and part of the &lt;a href=\"Shrouded%20Armor%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Shrouded Armor&lt;/a&gt; set found in . The gloves are notably worn by members of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Brotherhood%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Dark Brotherhood&lt;/a&gt;.\nSmithing.\nThe Shrouded Gloves can be upgraded at a &lt;a href=\"workbench\"&gt;workbench&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Leather%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Leather&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Arcane Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; perk, however they do not benefit from any &lt;a href=\"Smithing%20%28Skyrim%29%23Perks\"&gt;Smithing perks&lt;/a&gt;. This means the armor cannot be improved past &lt;a href=\"Smithing%20%28Skyrim%29%23Improvement\"&gt;flawless&lt;/a&gt; quality without boosting the Smithing skill over 100. This can be achieved by using &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Smithing%23Enchanting\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; items and/or &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Smithing%23Potions\"&gt;blacksmithing potions&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"fortify%20Smithing\"&gt;fortify Smithing&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnchanting.\nWearing this piece of armor grants the following skill bonuses:\nBackstab attacks require the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; to be both &lt;a href=\"Sneak%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;sneaking&lt;/a&gt; and undetected by the target.\nThe Shrouded Gloves cannot be disenchanted."}
{"id": "63474", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=63474", "title": "Shrouded Grove", "text": "Shrouded Grove is an area just north of &lt;a href=\"Korvanjund\"&gt;Korvanjund&lt;/a&gt; that contains a &lt;a href=\"Caves%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;cave&lt;/a&gt;.\nShrouded Grove Cave.\nInside the cave the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; will witness level-dependent animals fighting each other (typically &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Wolf%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;ice wolves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bear%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;bears&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Snow%20Bear%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;snow bears&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Snowy%20Sabre%20Cat%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;snowy sabre cats&lt;/a&gt;). After walking around the small corner, a &lt;a href=\"Spriggan%20Matron%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;spriggan matron&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"spriggan%20earth%20mother\"&gt;spriggan earth mother&lt;/a&gt; will emerge and attack the Dragonborn. With a high enough &lt;a href=\"Sneak%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Sneak&lt;/a&gt; skill, it is possible to see the inactive spriggan leaning against a tree trunk where it can easily be dispatched with a sneak attack; it will come alive and attack if detected.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Shalidor%27s%20Insights%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Shalidor's Insights&lt;/a&gt;.\nShrouded Grove is a possible location for the book \"&lt;a href=\"Shalidor%27s%20Insights%20%28Book%29\"&gt;Shalidor's Insights&lt;/a&gt;\", which &lt;a href=\"Urag%20gro-Shub\"&gt;Urag gro-Shub&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"College%20of%20Winterhold%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;College of Winterhold&lt;/a&gt; may ask the Dragonborn to retrieve. It is found in a chest towards the back of the cave."}
