{"id": "24685", "revid": "27037352", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24685", "title": "Sickly Bernice", "text": "Sickly Bernice is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bretons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Breton&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Character%20Classes%20%28Oblivion%29%23Publican\"&gt;publican&lt;/a&gt; who owns an &lt;a href=\"Taverns%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Inn&lt;/a&gt; called &lt;a href=\"Sickly%20Bernice%27s%20Taphouse\"&gt;Sickly Bernice's Taphouse&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Dementia\"&gt;Demented&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0part of &lt;a href=\"New%20Sheoth\"&gt;New Sheoth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crucible\"&gt;Crucible&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"A%20Liquid%20Solution\"&gt;A Liquid Solution&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe tells the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; that she is severely ill and needs somebody to get her the supposed cure,\u00a0aquanostrum,\u00a0from &lt;a href=\"Knotty%20Bramble\"&gt;Knotty Bramble&lt;/a&gt; or she will die.\nAfter the Hero of Kvatch gets her the cure she will thank and reward them with the &lt;a href=\"Circlet%20of%20Verdure\"&gt;Circlet of Verdure&lt;/a&gt;. After a few days she will ask them to return to the bramble again because her cure has run out, this repeats continually and she will not be cured.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20of%20Paranoia\"&gt;The Lady of Paranoia&lt;/a&gt;.\nBernice is one of the people that can be tortured for info on &lt;a href=\"Ma%27zaddha\"&gt;Ma'zaddha&lt;/a&gt;. She will say that he has been seen meeting with &lt;a href=\"Nelrene\"&gt;Nelrene&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\n\"Sickly Bernice, proprietor. Don't get too close now. You might catch what I have.\"\n\"Hello again... talk to me while you can. I don't think I've got too long.\""}
{"id": "22102", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22102", "title": "Sickly Bernice's Taphouse", "text": "Sickly Bernice's Taphouse is an &lt;a href=\"Taverns%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0on the south side of &lt;a href=\"Crucible\"&gt;Crucible&lt;/a&gt; that is run by &lt;a href=\"Sickly%20Bernice\"&gt;Sickly Bernice&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Rest%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Beds&lt;/a&gt; are available for 20 a night. The inn is the starting point for the quest \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Liquid%20Solution\"&gt;A Liquid Solution&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nOut back, there is an urn that is sunk in some sewage inside a broken crate; the key to which can be found with a \"&lt;a href=\"Faded%20Note%20%28Shivering%20Isles%29\"&gt;Faded Note&lt;/a&gt;\" on a rooftop in Crucible that describes it. The urn contains some loot, special wine and money.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"A%20Liquid%20Solution\"&gt;A Liquid Solution&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe owner of Sickly Bernice's Taphouse in &lt;a href=\"Crucible\"&gt;Crucible&lt;/a&gt; Sickly Bernice, asks for help in curing her fatal disease. She was told by a man that if he were to let him stay for free he would tell her the cure."}
