{"id": "860732", "revid": "25356303", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=860732", "title": "Siege Warfare (Covenant)", "text": "Siege Warfare is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nWalkthrough.\nHaving spoken to Bugbesh to deliver amunitions during the previous quest, Bugbesh now tasks the Vestige with using some of the siege equipment. Three types of catapults, ballistae, and trebuchets can be used to advance in the quest. While not required to advance the quest, hot oil can also be used to douse two targets in flaming oil to learn how the oil works. &lt;a href=\"Jaleel\"&gt;Jaleel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Marc%20Sauvage\"&gt;Marc Sauvage&lt;/a&gt; can also be spoken to for a tutorial on the siege weapons.\nAfter using one of each of the ranged siege weapons return to Bugbesh to be given a Practice Repair Kit. Use it on one of the damaged pieces of siege equipment and then speak to &lt;a href=\"Aurorelle%20Varin\"&gt;Aurorelle Varin&lt;/a&gt; to complete the quest."}
{"id": "860736", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=860736", "title": "Siege Warfare (Dominion)", "text": "Siege Warfare is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in ."}
{"id": "860735", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=860735", "title": "Siege Warfare (Pact)", "text": "Siege Warfare is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available to be initiated from &lt;a href=\"Adalmor\"&gt;Adalmor&lt;/a&gt; once the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Welcome%20to%20Cyrodiil%20%28Pact%29\"&gt;Welcome to Cyrodiil&lt;/a&gt;\" is completed. It details the siege mechanics of the game's Cyrodiil campaigns.\nBackground.\n\"I've reached the siege range. Adalmor advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Looks-Forward and Lirtis to learn more about the weapons.\"\nWalkthrough.\nThe prerequisites for this quest are to complete \"Welcome to Cyrodiil,\" available to a character exclusively after obtaining a tenth level. The quest giver is Adalmor, located south of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Morrowind%20Gate\"&gt;Northern Morrowind Gate&lt;/a&gt; entrance, at a siege range.\n\"Yes? What is it?\"\nThe next objective would be to use the siege engines, trebuchet, ballista, and catapult, at the siege range on the dummies. Optionally, the player may talk to Walks-Forward and Lirtis Githalvel about the mechanisms of each of the siege engines and their relation to Cyrodiil campaigns.\n\"Your skill with siege weapons will make a difference in many battles. Learn to use them here.\"\n\"If you remember that gates are a keep's weak points, you know what tool to use to break in.\"\nAfter practice on the dummies is finished, the next objective would be to speak with Adalmor.\n\"Done already?\"\nAdalmor may be questioned again.\n\"Go on\u2015repair one of those siege weapons.\"\nTo repair a siege weapon using the practice repair kit, one would have to slot it on the quickslots tab of their inventory, then use it from the quickslot in an interactable distance. After repairing the siege weapon, one should speak with Galsi Mavani to conclude the quest.\n\"You are always welcome here, warrior.\""}
