{"id": "1077384", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1077384", "title": "Sigil Shop", "text": "Sigil Shop is an in-game digital marketplace in that allows players to purchase arcane &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nSigils.\nSigils are a form of &lt;a href=\"currency\"&gt;currency&lt;/a&gt; which can be earned by completing &lt;a href=\"Event%20Quests\"&gt;Event Quests&lt;/a&gt; and can only be used in the Sigil Shop. Sigils can be used in the store to purchase &lt;a href=\"Crafting%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;crafting&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt; materials as well as arcane items with a guaranteed bonus enchantment."}
{"id": "178959", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=178959", "title": "Sigil Stone", "text": "Sigil Stone may refer to:"}
{"id": "3073", "revid": "25646820", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3073", "title": "Sigil Stone (Oblivion)", "text": "A Sigil Stone is the object that keeps &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Gate%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Oblivion Gates&lt;/a&gt; open. They are found inside the &lt;a href=\"Sigilium%20Sanguis\"&gt;Sigilium Sanguis&lt;/a&gt;, at the top of the largest tower, in the planes of &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20%28Realm%29\"&gt;Oblivion&lt;/a&gt;. Once the stone is removed, it shuts the gate it was supporting and transports the player back to &lt;a href=\"Tamriel\"&gt;Tamriel&lt;/a&gt;, next to the now-destroyed gate. If placed somewhere outside of a container, a sigil stone rotates slowly and emits a mechanical sound not unlike the ambient sound inside of the Sigilium Sanguis room it came from. Sparks continuously appear near the surface of the stone, are pulled in, and vanish. If multiple stones are placed together, they rotate independently and do not synchronize. If they are moved around using the grab function, the sparks will stay for a few animation cycles in the previous location.\nUsefulness.\nOnce removed, Sigil Stones are placed in the &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;Inventory&lt;/a&gt;. They can be used to &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;enchant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jewelry%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Each stone can provide one of two possible effects: a defensive constant effect on jewelry or armor, or an offensive effect, that expends charges, on weapons. The constant effects never need to be recast; they also stack with newly cast effects.\nSoul Gems can only be used by members of the Mages Guild of Apprentice or higher rank, at the Arcane University. By contrast, anyone can use Sigil Stones to enchant other items in their inventory.\nWith Soul Gems on weapons, multiple enchantments or a radius of effect can be selected; Sigil Stones cannot do either. Sigil Stones can give a slightly greater amount of Absorb Health (25 instead of 22) than a Grand Soul Gem, but much less elemental damage (25 rather than 40).\nFor armor, the outlook is much brighter. Soul Gems give a maximum of 9% elemental shields, but Transcendent Sigil Stones (albeit only available at and after player level 17) can provide 25% as a constant effect.\nVariants.\nSigil Stones' enchantments vary in effect and quality based on the players level when the stone is obtained. All stones have a name prefix which refers to how powerful the enchantment will be, in order from weakest to strongest:\nPossible effects.\nThe 30 possible effects are as follows:"}
{"id": "1062020", "revid": "28207777", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1062020", "title": "Sigil Stone (Oblivion Mobile)", "text": "A Sigil Stone is a magical item that is used to hold open an &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Gate\"&gt;Oblivion Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Champion%20of%20Cyrodiil\"&gt;Champion of Cyrodiil&lt;/a&gt; enters the &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Gate\"&gt;Oblivion Gate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Bruma%20%28Oblivion%20Mobile%29\"&gt;Bruma&lt;/a&gt; in order to steal its Sigil Stone. The Stone is later used to open a portal to &lt;a href=\"Mankar%20Camoran%20%28Oblivion%20Mobile%29\"&gt;Mankar Camoran's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Gaiar%20Alata%20%28Oblivion%20Mobile%29\"&gt;Paradise&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "672284", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=672284", "title": "Sigil Stone (Online)", "text": "A Sigil Stone is an item used to power a &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Portal\"&gt;Daedric Portal&lt;/a&gt;. In , this happens in several different quests."}
{"id": "59665", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=59665", "title": "Sigil Stone (Skyrim)", "text": "Sigil Stones are magical objects that open portals between &lt;a href=\"Nirn\"&gt;Nirn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20%28Realm%29\"&gt;Oblivion&lt;/a&gt;. The Sigil Stone is a necessary ingredient for the forging of &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Armor%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Daedric armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Daedra%20Heart%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Daedra hearts&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Atronach%20Forge\"&gt;Atronach Forge&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Midden\"&gt;The Midden&lt;/a&gt; beneath the &lt;a href=\"College%20of%20Winterhold%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;College of Winterhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nTo obtain a sigil stone, the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; (after reaching a &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; level of 90 or higher) must seek out &lt;a href=\"Phinis%20Gestor\"&gt;Phinis Gestor&lt;/a&gt;, an Expert &lt;a href=\"Conjurer%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; of the College of Winterhold. Phinis provides them with &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Unbound%20Dremora\"&gt;a summoning spell&lt;/a&gt; that calls forth an &lt;a href=\"unbound%20dremora\"&gt;unbound dremora&lt;/a&gt;. Heading to the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Attainment\"&gt;Hall of Attainment&lt;/a&gt;, the Dragonborn needs to cast the spell in a circle of candles. The dremora refuses to obey mortals' orders, and he must be defeated twice, after which he will submit to the Dragonborn's orders. Then, the Dragonborn demands that the dremora return to Oblivion and bring back a sigil stone. He obeys and the stone is acquired.\nIn exchange for the sigil stone, Phinis Gestor teaches the Dragonborn &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Thrall\"&gt;Flame Thrall&lt;/a&gt;, as well as now offering to sell other master-level &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;. The sigil stone will be returned to the Dragonborn after learning the new spell.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20Ritual%20Spell\"&gt;Conjuration Ritual Spell&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce level 90 Conjuration is reached, a new dialogue option appears with &lt;a href=\"Phinis%20Gestor\"&gt;Phinis Gestor&lt;/a&gt;: \"What else is there to be learned about Conjuration magic?\" He mentions that, in order to give any higher-level Conjuration spells, he must have a sigil stone from an &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Gate%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Oblivion gate&lt;/a&gt;. He then teaches the &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Unbound%20Dremora\"&gt;Summon Unbound Dremora&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Tomes%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;. He tells the Dragonborn to climb up to the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Attainment\"&gt;Hall of Attainment&lt;/a&gt;, use the spell, then defeat the summoned, unbound &lt;a href=\"Dremora%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;dremora&lt;/a&gt;."}
