{"id": "954103", "revid": "32638003", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=954103", "title": "Signal Fire Sprint", "text": "Signal Fire Sprint is a repeatable daily &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available during &lt;a href=\"New%20Life%20Festival%20%28Online%29\"&gt;New Life Festival&lt;/a&gt; in .\nWalkthrough.\nAll fires must be lit within 60 seconds. The fires are all on the platform walkways in the area. If failed, the run can be repeated from Aubatha. \nLighting all four Signal Fires in less than 35 seconds grants the &lt;a href=\"Signal%20Fire%20Zephyr\"&gt;Signal Fire Zephyr&lt;/a&gt; achievement.\nUsing &lt;a href=\"Rapid%20Maneuver\"&gt;Rapid Maneuver&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sprint\"&gt;sprint&lt;/a&gt;ing should be enough to earn the achievement. If needed, &lt;a href=\"The%20Steed%20%28Online%29\"&gt;The Steed&lt;/a&gt; Mundus Stone and the &lt;a href=\"Rign%20of%20the%20Wild%20Hunt\"&gt;Rign of the Wild Hunt&lt;/a&gt; can also be used to increase &lt;a href=\"movement%20speed\"&gt;movement speed&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsing &lt;a href=\"Essence%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Essence of Speed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Potions%20%28Online%29\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; and forward Roll Dodge ability while sprinting also makes achievement reachable."}
{"id": "986826", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=986826", "title": "Signal Tower Orders", "text": "Signal Tower Orders is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20%28Orsinium%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in .\nContents.\nLoyal &lt;a href=\"Bretons%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Bretons&lt;/a&gt;,\nNo matter how hard the wind blows or how fast the snow falls, we have a job to do. &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Henrisa\"&gt;Captain Henrisa&lt;/a&gt; and her fleet will be in range soon. Make sure the signal fire stays lit until you see the sails of the fleet, then douse the fire.\nThis blasted storm may disrupt her plans a bit, but I'd say the weather will work in our favor for a change."}
{"id": "615070", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=615070", "title": "Signals of Dominion", "text": "Signals of Dominion is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . &lt;a href=\"Aldmeri%20Dominion%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Aldmeri Dominion&lt;/a&gt; forces have captured &lt;a href=\"Farwatch%20Tower\"&gt;Farwatch Tower&lt;/a&gt;. They're using the tower to signal their fleet at sea.\nWalkthrough.\nOn the road near the &lt;a href=\"Farwatch%20Tower%20Wayshrine\"&gt;Farwatch Tower Wayshrine&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; will find an injured &lt;a href=\"Orsimer%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Orsimer&lt;/a&gt; named Sergeant Muzbar. He says the Dominion soldiers have taken the Farwatch Tower and are planning another attack. A scout has found out they are passing messages between the commanders and using the tower to signal their ships. Bring one of those messages to Captain Gilame.\nThe Dominion camp isn't far away, head over there and fight the Dominion soldiers on the way. Fight the commander holding the message, and then sneak away over the bridge to find the captain.\nExplain to her about the message, and after reading it she finds out the Dominion is planning a full-scale attack. We must stop the commander, but after hearing he has been eliminated, she realize this will buy them precious time. She gives the Vestige a storm rune to put out the fires in the tower. Gilame wants them to meet her on the shore after the fires are out.\nHead to the tower and deal with any enemy that attack. Go inside and up the stairs to the top, put the storm stone in the fires and they will all be extinguished. Return to the captain and she is pleased with the work. This will give them time to bring in reinforcements, good job! She rewards the Vestige with a pair of &lt;a href=\"Lion%20Guard%20Poleyns\"&gt;Lion Guard Poleyns&lt;/a&gt; and some ."}
{"id": "921004", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=921004", "title": "Signed in Blood", "text": "Signed in Blood is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Dark%20Brotherhood%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nBackground.\n\"To prove myself to the Dark Brotherhood, Speaker Terenus wants me to murder the Imperial noble named Quintus Jarol.\"\nWalkthrough.\nUpon completing \"&lt;a href=\"Voices%20in%20the%20Dark\"&gt;Voices in the Dark&lt;/a&gt;,\" &lt;a href=\"Speaker%20Terenus%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Speaker Terenus&lt;/a&gt; will tell you to kill a noble named &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Quintus%20Jarol\"&gt;Lord Quintus Jarol&lt;/a&gt; to complete your initiation into the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Brotherhood%20%28Online%20Faction%29\"&gt;Dark Brotherhood&lt;/a&gt;. Lord Jarol has an estate northwest of &lt;a href=\"Anvil%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Anvil&lt;/a&gt;. If asked for advice on how to get in, Terenus will tell you about a smuggler's tunnel in &lt;a href=\"The%20Withered%20Rose\"&gt;The Withered Rose&lt;/a&gt;, a hostel south of the estate. \nHead to the Withered Rose and break into the cellar; the door will be locked. Once inside, head through the door to the Smuggler Tunnels. These tunnels will be filled with smugglers and traps, so mind your step and stay hidden to avoid a bounty. At the end, head up the ladder to the estate courtyard. From there, sneak your way past the guards to the estate building and pick the lock to get in. Proceed ahead and up the stairs, and you will find a \"&lt;a href=\"Letter%20from%20the%20Governor\"&gt;Letter from the Governor&lt;/a&gt;\" that talks about secret rooms beneath the estate. \nHead down and into the mansion's wine cellar. In there, on the desk, you will find a \"&lt;a href=\"Contractor%27s%20Note\"&gt;Contractor's Note&lt;/a&gt;\". This note will tell you how to get into the secret chambers: there are three fake wine casks. You must knock on the two closest to the lanterns. There are two casks to which this applies; knock on both of them to open a passage in a wine cask on the side of the room farthest from the entrance. \nProceed to sneak through the halls; there will be guards to avoid and trip wires to watch out for, but no branching paths to confuse you. Along the way, you will overhear conversations between Lord Jarol, &lt;a href=\"Governor%20Fortunata%20ap%20Dugal\"&gt;Governor Fortunata ap Dugal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Count%20Carolus%20Aquilarios\"&gt;Count Carolus Aquilarios&lt;/a&gt; about a recent series of murders. Continue through the halls and into the caverns below; ad the end of the caves, you will find Lord Jarol. The Governor and the Count have just left. You can either sneak up on Jarol and use the Blade of Woe to kill him, or you can attack him regularly, though the latter will get you a bounty. Either way, once Jarol is dead, leave the caves and return to Speaker Terenus in the lighthouse to finish your initiation.\nTerenus will tell you where to find the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Brotherhood%20Sanctuary%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Dark Brotherhood Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;; it is in the north of the region, off the Gold Road. The password is \"Sublime, my brother.\" Head there and proceed inside. Once inside the sanctuary, seek out a woman named Astara; she will be in the central chamber. Speak with her to finish the quest and start the next one, \"&lt;a href=\"Welcome%20Home\"&gt;Welcome Home&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
{"id": "882697", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=882697", "title": "Signet of Sancre Tor", "text": "The Signet of Sancre Tor is a &lt;a href=\"Jewelry%20%28Online%29%23Rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in obtained from &lt;a href=\"Varen%20Aquilarios%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Varen Aquilarios&lt;/a&gt; after completing the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Shadow%20of%20Sancre%20Tor\"&gt;Shadow of Sancre Tor&lt;/a&gt;.\" The Signet spent years inside &lt;a href=\"Sancre%20Tor%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Sancre Tor&lt;/a&gt; which has caused it to develop a natural reflection to &lt;a href=\"Magicka%20%28Online%29\"&gt;magicka&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n\"After years in the heavily enchanted vaults of Sancre Tor, this ring actively deflects magicka around it.\"\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Shadow%20of%20Sancre%20Tor\"&gt;Shadow of Sancre Tor&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; must go to Sancre Tor to recover the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Kings%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Amulet of Kings&lt;/a&gt; before &lt;a href=\"Molag%20Bal%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Molag Bal&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Black%20Worm%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Order of the Black Worm&lt;/a&gt; find it. The Signet of Sancre Tor is awarded to the Vestige by Aquilarios after completing the quest."}
{"id": "694142", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=694142", "title": "Signet of the Worm", "text": "The Signet of the Worm is a &lt;a href=\"Jewelry%20%28Online%29%23Rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in obtained from the &lt;a href=\"Varen%20Aquilarios%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Prophet&lt;/a&gt; after completing the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Castle%20of%20the%20Worm%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Castle of the Worm&lt;/a&gt;.\" The Signet is one of many worn by senior cultists of the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Black%20Worm%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Order of the Black Worm&lt;/a&gt; and is stained with \"necromantic fluids.\"\nDescription.\n\"Worn by the upper ranks of Mannimarco's followers, this simple ring is stained with necromantic fluids.\"\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Castle%20of%20the%20Worm%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Castle of the Worm&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; must travel to the &lt;a href=\"Castle%20of%20the%20Worm%20%28Location%29\"&gt;Castle of the Worm&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Coldharbour%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Coldharbour&lt;/a&gt; to rescue &lt;a href=\"Abnur%20Tharn%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Abnur Tharn&lt;/a&gt; who knows the location of &lt;a href=\"Sai%20Sahan%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Sai Sahan&lt;/a&gt;. The Signet is awarded to the Vestige by the Prophet after completing the quest."}
{"id": "19765", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19765", "title": "Signy Home-Wrecker", "text": "Signy Home-Wrecker is a member of the Sirens, an all female gang of thieves that operates out of &lt;a href=\"Anvil%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Anvil&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Faustina%20Cartia\"&gt;Faustina Cartia&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tsarrina\"&gt;Tsarrina&lt;/a&gt;, she and the rest of the gang attract married men into the wilderness to rob them of their valuables. She resides on &lt;a href=\"Gweden%20Farm\"&gt;Gweden Farm&lt;/a&gt; southwest of Anvil.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Siren%27s%20Deception\"&gt;The Siren's Deception&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Maelona\"&gt;Maelona&lt;/a&gt; wants the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; to help her husband &lt;a href=\"Gogan\"&gt;Gogan&lt;/a&gt; by defeating a gang of women who lure men outside of town to rob them. She promises 100 gold to get back a ring Gogan lost. Travel to &lt;a href=\"The%20Flowing%20Bowl\"&gt;The Flowing Bowl&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nStarted in &lt;a href=\"Anvil%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Anvil&lt;/a&gt; through a &lt;a href=\"Rumors%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;rumor&lt;/a&gt;, undercover agents of the &lt;a href=\"City%20Guard%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Anvil Watch&lt;/a&gt; are working to track down an all-female band of &lt;a href=\"Thief%20%28Class%29\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; that seduce married men, lure them out of town, and rob them.\nIf the Hero is a female talk to her and she will tell them to talk to her leader Faustina. If they are a man she will approach them with the offer of a \"night of fun.\"\nDialogue.\nIf the Hero is male\n\"I haven't seen you here before. Awww, and you're all alone too. How sad. Well, if you're up to it, I think we can solve that little problem. You see, me and Faustina here are lonely too, and we've been looking for someone. You look like just what we need. I'll tell you what. We have a cozy farmhouse not far from here where we could... well... get to know each other much, much better. I'll mark it down on your map, just so you won't forget where to find us. Meet us there around 11 in the evening. I can promise you a night of fun you won't soon forget.\"\n\"Trust me when I say we'll give you a night to remember.\"\nIf approached again:\n\"Patience. We'll have... all night.\"\nIf the Hero is female\n\"Talk to Faustina. She's got a proposition for you.\""}
