{"id": "62452", "revid": "26213507", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62452", "title": "Silent Moons Camp", "text": "Silent Moons Camp is a bandit settlement, found northwest of the city of &lt;a href=\"Whiterun%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Whiterun&lt;/a&gt;, in the &lt;a href=\"Whiterun%20Hold\"&gt;Whiterun Hold&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nSilent Moons Camp is composed of the outside area and small cave system accessed by a door in the wall near the base. The camp is home to a group of bandits whose leader is trying to learn the secrets of the Lunar Forge.\nThe most prominent feature of this location is the &lt;a href=\"Lunar%20Forge\"&gt;Lunar Forge&lt;/a&gt;, which is at the top of the outside structure. Inside the cave is where the &lt;a href=\"Bandits%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Bandit Leader&lt;/a&gt; has set up their headquarters. At the end of the cave is a locked door, leading to the bandit leader's room and treasure. The cave entrance is a door to the right of the stairs leading to the Lunar Forge.\nInside the leader's room is a ladder leading up to an otherwise difficult to access chest in the topside ruins behind a gate that can only be activated by the pull chain nearby. This can also be accessed by scaling the rocks above the ruined wall that leads to the tower which houses the chest.\nThe camp has the usual assortment of random potions, gold, and food items."}
{"id": "72454", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=72454", "title": "Silent Moons Enchant", "text": "The Silent Moons Enchant is a weapon enchantment that can be learned by disenchanting &lt;a href=\"Lunar%20Weapons\"&gt;Lunar Weapons&lt;/a&gt; located at the &lt;a href=\"Lunar%20Forge\"&gt;Lunar Forge&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Moons%20Camp\"&gt;Silent Moons Camp&lt;/a&gt; northwest of &lt;a href=\"Whiterun%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Whiterun&lt;/a&gt;. This enchantment provides a damage bonus at night \"while the moons are out,\" and gives the enchanted weapon a green glow at night and during the day it makes the target of the weapon glow almost yellow.\nThe lunar weapons from which the Silent Moons Enchant can be obtained with three levels of the enchantment, based on player level. Level 1 does 10 points of damage, level 2 does 15 points, and level 3 does 20 points."}
