{"id": "115283", "revid": "5165253", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=115283", "title": "Silent Pilgrimage", "text": "Silent Pilgrimage is a &lt;a href=\"Tribunal%20Temple\"&gt;Tribunal Temple&lt;/a&gt; quest, available to the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt;, during the events of .\nWalkthrough.\nOnce the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; has solved the issue of the &lt;a href=\"Disease%20Carrier\"&gt;Disease Carrier&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Endryn%20Llethan\"&gt;Endryn Llethan&lt;/a&gt;, they may obtain a new quest from him. Llethan asks that the Nerevarine undertakes the Silent Pilgrimage from &lt;a href=\"Vivec%20City%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Vivec City&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Sanctus%20Shrine%20%28Location%29\"&gt;Sanctus Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, located west of &lt;a href=\"Dagon%20Fel\"&gt;Dagon Fel&lt;/a&gt;. The Nerevarine can not speak to anyone during the pilgrimage.\nA Silent Pilgrim.\nThe Nerevarine should reach the shrine by journey on foot to the northern island, on which the Shrine can be found. However, the Nerevarine may shorten the journey by using a combination of &lt;a href=\"Almsivi%20Intervention\"&gt;Almsivi Intervention&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Intervention%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Divine Intervention&lt;/a&gt; (teleporting and walking between the various locations).\nThere are various other methods to get there:\nEnding the silence.\nOnce the Nerevarine has arrived at Sanctus Shrine Island, west of Dagon Fel and south of &lt;a href=\"Vas\"&gt;Vas&lt;/a&gt;, they must activate the shrine, the vow of silence is achieved and ends there. Now, the Hero is able to speak to anyone, and may return to Llethan to complete the quest.\nRewards.\nLlethan will reward the Nerevarine with four &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Books%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; books:"}
