{"id": "616595", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=616595", "title": "Silsailen Rescue", "text": "Silsailen Rescue is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . The town of &lt;a href=\"Silsailen\"&gt;Silsailen&lt;/a&gt; is under attack by imposters disguised as &lt;a href=\"First%20Auridon%20Marines\"&gt;First Auridon Marines&lt;/a&gt;. The townspeople suspect these men and women are part of a group called the &lt;a href=\"Veiled%20Heritance\"&gt;Veiled Heritance&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\n\"The town of Silsailen is under attack by imposters disguised as FIrst Auridon Marines. The townspeople suspect these men and are part of a group called the Veiled Heritance.\"\nWalkthrough.\nIf one comes close enough to &lt;a href=\"Silsailen\"&gt;Silsailen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ilemin\"&gt;Ilemin&lt;/a&gt; will run up to the &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; asking for help. Alternatively, one can go directly to &lt;a href=\"Elenwen%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Elenwen&lt;/a&gt; in order to start the quest. Ilemin will then say that the Veiled Heritance came to the town dressed like First Auridon Marines\u00a0and set fire to the buildings, directing you to speak with Elenwen, who organized the evacuation.\n\"You there. Please. Please help us!\"\n\"They've burned the town! Please, please help us!\"\nApproaching the town, villagers can be seen fleeing it and running towards a barn on the outskirts. Elenwen can be near the barn, next to a bridge on the top of the hill. Once spoken to, she will further explain on the Veiled Heritance's attack on the village and that she is &lt;a href=\"Canonreeve%20Valano\"&gt;Canonreeve Valano&lt;/a&gt;'s daughter. She will then ask you to speak with Teldur, her father's assistant.\n\"The Veiled Heritance is behind this madness, I'm sure of it!\"\nTeldur can be found at the center of the town kneeling beside the well. He instructs you to grab the bucket and douse the fires in order to save the villagers.\n\"Are you insane? Can't you see the town is under attack?\"\nThe bucket can be found beside the well and can be picked up when activated. Using it, go near the fires and activate it when the prompt shows up in order to put them out. Villagers will either be trapped inside the buildings or held hostage by the attackers. Defeating the enemies that threaten the villagers or putting out the fires at the entrance of the buildings will free them, and they will run outside of the town.\nOnce five villagers are saved, report back to Elenwen. She will be in the barn close to where she was previously standing and will thank the Vestige by giving them a gold reward.\n\"The fires are under control, thanks to you.\""}
{"id": "976886", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=976886", "title": "Silt-Strider Station", "text": "Silt-Strider Station is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20%28ESO%20Morrowind%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in .\nContents.\nWhy brave the dangers of the open road or pay the high costs of an unsettling sea voyage when you can travel overland in safety and comfort aboard a friendly &lt;a href=\"Silt%20Strider%20%28Online%29\"&gt;silt-strider&lt;/a&gt;? Why ride a caravan of questionable virtue when the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Mountain\"&gt;Red Mountain&lt;/a&gt; Company Express Silt-Strider Service is available at a fraction of the cost?\nVisit any of our Silt-Strider Stations, located conveniently in towns throughout &lt;a href=\"Vvardenfell%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Vvardenfell&lt;/a&gt;, and connect to destinations far and near. Want to leave the hustle of &lt;a href=\"Vivec%20City%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Vivec City&lt;/a&gt; behind? Travel to Balmora and see the canals, or visit the plantations of &lt;a href=\"Suran%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Suran&lt;/a&gt;! Stuck in the outskirts of &lt;a href=\"Gnisis%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Gnisis&lt;/a&gt;? It's just a short trip via the Caravaner Tower outside town and you can reach &lt;a href=\"Tel%20Mora%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Tel Mora&lt;/a&gt; before dinner!\nThe Red Mountain Company Express Silt-Strider Service, located at Caravaner Towers all across Vvardenfell, can get you where you need to go. Remember, when you climb aboard a silt-strider, your destination is just a hop, skip, and a jump away!"}
