{"id": "2498", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2498", "title": "The Changed Ones", "text": "The Changed Ones is a &lt;a href=\"book\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in and .\nContents.\nOf all the &lt;a href=\"et%27Ada\"&gt;et'Ada&lt;/a&gt; who wandered &lt;a href=\"Nirn\"&gt;Nirn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Trinimac\"&gt;Trinimac&lt;/a&gt; was the strongest. He, for a very long time, fooled the &lt;a href=\"Aldmer\"&gt;Aldmer&lt;/a&gt;i into thinking that tears were the best response to the Sundering. They cried and shamed our ancestors, especially the feminine &lt;a href=\"Altmer\"&gt;Altmer&lt;/a&gt;. They even took the Missing God's name in vain, calling his narratives into question. So one day &lt;a href=\"Boethiah\"&gt;Boethiah&lt;/a&gt;, Prince of Plots, precocious youth, tricked Trinimac to go into his mouth. Boethiah talked like Trinimac for awhile then, and gathered enough people to listen to him. Boethiah showed them the lies of the et'Ada, the &lt;a href=\"Aedra\"&gt;Aedra&lt;/a&gt;, and told them Trinimac was the biggest liar of all, saying all this with Trinimac's voice! Boethiah told the mass before him the Tri-Angled Truth. He showed them, with &lt;a href=\"Mephala\"&gt;Mephala&lt;/a&gt;, the rules of &lt;a href=\"Psijic%20Endeavor\"&gt;Psijic Endeavor&lt;/a&gt;. He taught them how to build houses, and what items they needed to bury in the corners. He demonstrated the right way to wear their skin. He performed the way to walk to achieve an exodus. Then Boethiah relieved himself of Trinimac right there on the ground before them to prove all the things he said were the truth. It was easy for his new people to become the Changed Ones."}
{"id": "878045", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=878045", "title": "The Charge of Evermore", "text": "The Charge of Evermore is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nBackground.\n\"Soldiers from Evermore were defeated at Murcien's Hamlet by a Reachman attack.\"\nWalkthrough.\nOn the docks of &lt;a href=\"Murcien%27s%20Hamlet\"&gt;Murcien's Hamlet&lt;/a&gt;, you will find a man named &lt;a href=\"Squire%20Theo%20Rocque\"&gt;Squire Theo Rocque&lt;/a&gt;. He will tell you that he and his liege &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Etienne%20Hu\"&gt;Sir Etienne Hu&lt;/a&gt; were sent here to protect the village, but that his liege has since fallen ill. He will ask for your help in fighting off the &lt;a href=\"Reachmen%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Reachmen&lt;/a&gt; here. The moment you are done talking, the village elder, &lt;a href=\"Medya%20Zurric\"&gt;Medya Zurric&lt;/a&gt;, will show up and tell Theo that Sir Etienne is being taken care of and will soon rest easily. \nTalk to Theo again and he will tell you what happened here; he and his soldiers came to the defense of the villagers, but they were slaughtered and the Reachmen managed to take over the town. He will then head off to go check on Sir Etienne, telling you to hold the line. Check the fortifications on both sides of the docks. On the eastern side, you will notice that the fortifications are on fire; grab a bucket of water and put it out. On the west side, you will be attacked by several waves of Reachmen, so you will have to fend these off.\nOnce the fortifications on both sides have been checked, head to the north side of town, to Medya Zurric's home. You will have to fight your way through a horde of Reachmen to get there. Inside, you will find Theo by the side of Sir Etienne's body. Sir Etienne seems to have been murdered with his own weapon. Theo will ask you to look around the house to see if there are any clues regarding who killed the man. Examine the body, the scene at the dining table, the wash basket on the other side of the room and the book lying by the bookshelf. You will find that Sir Etienne's wounds had been tended to, that he was dining with three people here and that someone here was reading a book containing Medya Zurric's family history. The book on her family history mentions that she survived the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Drake%27s%20Invasion\"&gt;Black Drake's Invasion&lt;/a&gt; and that she had a son.\n\"&lt;Blood is scattered in tiny droplets all over the surfaces. There are three bowls near the table. It appears as though Sir Etienne had his broken leg propped on the extra chair on his side of the table.&gt;\"\n\"&lt;The basin's interior is damp, and its edges are smudged with fresh blood stains.&gt;\"\nTake this information to Theo and he will note that it seems likely that Medya is either another victim or will know about the culprit. She is not here though; her apprentice &lt;a href=\"Rolbert%20Foucher\"&gt;Rolbert Foucher&lt;/a&gt; is down by the docks and may be able to supply more information. Speak with him there and he will tell you that Medya did indeed live through the Black Drake's Invasion, but that he has never heard of her having a son. He will also tell you that since the invasion, Medya has been something of a leader to the village, and that the reachmen have not raided here even though they have raided in other places. He will suggest looking for Medya in the homes; she might be treating people there. \nIn the abandoned house in the west of town, you will find a &lt;a href=\"The%20Reachmen%20are%20Coming%21\"&gt;note&lt;/a&gt; that mentions Medya telling someone that the Reachmen would be coming. It will mention her coming down from the river covered in blood. Head to the river and you will find an altar to &lt;a href=\"Hircine%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Hircine&lt;/a&gt; there.\n\"&lt;Scattered around this grisly totem are Hagraven feathers and spears of blood, both new and old.&gt;\"\nTake this information back to Theo at Medya's house; when you approach the house, you will hear Theo's voice saying Medya's here. Head inside and a spell will be put on Theo, making him fall to the ground. Medya's son &lt;a href=\"Labhraidh\"&gt;Labhraidh&lt;/a&gt; is here and is hostile; kill him and Theo will recover. Theo will accuse Medya of having killed Sir Etienne; speak with him and he will ask you whether Medya should be killed on the spot or whether she should get a trial. Whichever option you choose will end the quest."}
