{"id": "640507", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=640507", "title": "The Corpse Horde", "text": "The Corpse Horde is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . The &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; encountered an injured &lt;a href=\"Lion%20Guard\"&gt;Lion Guard&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Malik%20Nasir\"&gt;Sir Malik Nasir&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Merovec%27s%20Folly\"&gt;Merovec's Folly&lt;/a&gt;. He wants them to stop the &lt;a href=\"Bloodthorn%20Cultist\"&gt;Bloodthorn cultists&lt;/a&gt; from desecrating the dead Lion Guard soldiers.\nWalkthrough.\nSir Malik explains they were working with the wizard &lt;a href=\"Gabrielle%20Benele\"&gt;Benele&lt;/a&gt; when the zombies attacked. They lost track of her and now the cultists are desecrating the dead, which is considered an affront to &lt;a href=\"Tu%27whacca\"&gt;Tu'whacca&lt;/a&gt;. Offer to help and he'll explain that the cultists raise the dead soldiers to zombies.\nUsing this sacred emblem, one can sanctify the corpses and that will prevent them to be raised as undead. He gives it to the Vestige. Now go to the ruins at Merovec's Folly.\nSearch the ruins for five dead soldiers and use the emblem to sanctify the corpses. When all are done return to Sir Malik, now at &lt;a href=\"Lion%20Guard%20Redoubt\"&gt;Lion Guard Redoubt&lt;/a&gt;.\nFind Sir Malik to let him know the task is done. He is relieved the Vestige has completed his business."}
{"id": "34122", "revid": "26308784", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34122", "title": "The Corpse and the Skooma Pipe", "text": "The Corpse and the Skooma Pipe is a quest available in . The quest starts only when the Nerevarine is intrigued enough by the note and the skooma pipe on the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Ernil%20Omoran\"&gt;Ernil Omoran&lt;/a&gt; to go and find &lt;a href=\"Tsiya\"&gt;Tsiya&lt;/a&gt;, to whom the note is directed and who ownes the skooma pipe.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nWhile traveling on the road to Caldera from Balmora on the first sign post a large arched rock should be in view. Almost underneath it there is the body of Ernil Omoran. Loot &lt;a href=\"Tsiya%27s%20Skooma%20Pipe\"&gt;Tsiya's Skooma Pipe&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Note%20From%20Ernil\"&gt;Note From Ernil&lt;/a&gt;, then head back to Balmora to find &lt;a href=\"Tsiya\"&gt;Tsiya&lt;/a&gt;.\nTsiya's house is on the west side, facing the river, refer to the map if it can't be found. There is a 50-point lock on the door, so if incapable of lockpicking it head to &lt;a href=\"Galbedir\"&gt;Galbedir&lt;/a&gt; of the Balmora Mages Guild, buy a &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Ondusi%27s%20Unhinging\"&gt;Scroll of Ondusi's Unhinging&lt;/a&gt; and use it on the door. She will on the top floor.\nOnce inside talk to Tsiya about \"specific people\". Further dialogue will conclude with her learning of the death of Ernil. There are two choices from there: Give the note and skooma pipe back to Tsiya for a reward of 10 &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Sugar%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;moon sugars&lt;/a&gt;, 50 gold and her thanks, or tell her nothing was on the body and keep the skooma pipe."}
{"id": "849068", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=849068", "title": "The Corrupted Stone", "text": "The Corrupted Stone is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nBackground.\n\"The guardian star sign of the Warrior has failed to appear to protect the mortal world from the Serpent. One of the Star-Gazers needs help uncovering what might be happening.\"\nWalkthrough.\nIn the north of &lt;a href=\"Belkarth%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Belkarth&lt;/a&gt;, you will find a woman named Qasna at-Toura. She will tell you that Erold is researching something interesting for the &lt;a href=\"Star-Gazers\"&gt;Star-Gazers&lt;/a&gt; that you might want to help with. Erold can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Crossroads%20Tavern\"&gt;Crossroads Tavern&lt;/a&gt;; speak with him and he will tell you that this is not the first time the &lt;a href=\"Celestial\"&gt;Celestial&lt;/a&gt;s have come down to Craglorn. He thinks they are connected to artifacts called the &lt;a href=\"Apex%20Stones\"&gt;Apex Stones&lt;/a&gt;. However, to get to the Apex Stones, you need a &lt;a href=\"Nedic\"&gt;Nedic&lt;/a&gt; amulet, which are hard to come by as the Nedes disappeared centuries ago. He suspects one may be found at the ruins of &lt;a href=\"Shada%27s%20Tear\"&gt;Shada's Tear&lt;/a&gt;.\nHead for &lt;a href=\"Mtharnaz\"&gt;Mtharnaz&lt;/a&gt;, southeast of the &lt;a href=\"Bangkorai%20Gate\"&gt;Bangkorai Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Many Nedes were kept as slaves here back in the day. You will find the amulet you need in the westernmost room. Once you take it, &lt;a href=\"The%20Thief%20%28Celestial%29\"&gt;the Thief&lt;/a&gt; will appear and tell you that this amulet is capable of more than just opening the way to the Warrior's apex stone. She will tell you to charge it at the Mundus Stones of the Lord, the Lady and the Steed. \nThe Steed is just north of your current location, the Warrior is northwest of &lt;a href=\"The%20Seeker%27s%20Archive%20%28Location%29\"&gt;the Seeker's Archive&lt;/a&gt; and the lady is on an island in the lake south of &lt;a href=\"Dragonstar%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Dragonstar&lt;/a&gt;. Upon charging the amulet at the first of these stones, the Thief will appear and tell you that &lt;a href=\"The%20Serpent%20%28Celestial%29\"&gt;the Serpent&lt;/a&gt; poisoned the Warrior's mind, but that hopefully with the help of the charged Skystone Amulet, he can be brought back. At the second mundus stone, the Thief will tell you that the Serpent's followers, the &lt;a href=\"Scaled%20Court\"&gt;Scaled Court&lt;/a&gt;, have found and corrupted the Warrior's Apex Stone, but she believes that with the power of the Lord, the Lady and the Steed, he can be brought back. At the third Mundus Stone, the Thief will tell you to head to Kardala where the Apex Stone rests, and use your amulet to cleanse it. Kardala can be found in the middle of where you found the mundus stones. \nOnce inside Kardala, proceed to the northwest. There, you will run into the Thief Again; she will tell you that beyond this door, the Warrior's charges will guide your way. Head in and fight your way through the dungeon's boss, &lt;a href=\"Izrunath%20the%20Corruptor\"&gt;Izrunath the Corruptor&lt;/a&gt;. Take care though, as this boss is very strong and will summon serpents to help him in battle. Once the boss lies dead, cleanse the Apex Stone. &lt;a href=\"The%20Lord%20%28Celestial%29\"&gt;The Lord&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20%28Celestial%29\"&gt;the Lady&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Steed%20%28Celestial%29\"&gt;the Steed&lt;/a&gt; wull appear to talk sense into the Warrior. This will work; the apex stone will be cleansed. However, afterward, the Serpent will appear to tell you that the Warrior is trapped in mortal form and is still under his control. \nWith this, head back to Belkarth and speak with Star-Gazer Erold to finish the quest."}
